description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and motivated nurse with strong clinical leadership skills and expertise to join the Bone Marrow Transplant nursing team as a Clinical Nurse Specialist. St Georges BMT service has grown substantially creating a need for a second Stem Cell Transplant CNS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will share responsibility for the coordination of patients’ pre and post care undergoing allogeneic and autologous bone marrow and stem cell transplants. With clinical commitment both pre and post transplant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide education to junior haematology/oncology nurses and the wider MDT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide professional development, with close links the the Royal Marsden school and it&#39;s Advanced Nurse pathways. We are seeking highly motivated candidates with substantial BMT/Haematology experience who are passionate about this patient group and developing the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Paska- Haematology and Oncology Matron-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Julie.paska@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
